Java Variables
----------------
Instance Var: 
	if variable value is varied from object to object.
	separate copy will create for every object.
	a)using object only

Static Var:  static keyword
	If variable value is not varied from object to object
	only one copy will create at class level
	and shared to all object.
	a)using class Name
	b)using Object Name
	c)directly in static context
Local var:
	within method declaring and use- temp
